      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 54: `shouldSend()` sleeps on the media send path to simulate jitter. This blocks RTP sender threads directly and can distort encoder pacing, RTCP timing, and call behavior beyond the intended network impairment. Prefer a queue/pacer model for jitter simulation, or limit this class to packet loss/bandwidth drops and leave delay/jitter to the namespace-based netem tests.",
