      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 635: The network simulator silently drops RTP after SRTP/ICE processing has produced the final packet, but it returns `buf_size` as if the packet was successfully written. This makes callers believe bytes were transmitted and can hide send-path failures from RTP pacing/statistics. More importantly, this simulator is never attached from `NetworkSimRegistry`, so the documented in-process test API cannot affect real media sockets. Wire the registry into RTP session/socket construction using the call id and media type, or remove the registry/documentation until there is a real integration point.",
